Metadata-Version: 2.4
Name: slm
Version: 0.1.0
Summary: Questionary-based symlink target migration tool
Author: niceday
Requires-Python: >=3.9
Description-Content-Type: text/markdown
Requires-Dist: questionary<3.0,>=2.0.1

slm â€” Symlink Target Migrator (Questionary)

Quickstart
- Install dependencies: `pip install -e .`
- Run interactive UI: `slm`

Notes
- Default Data root: `~/Developer/Data` (override with `--data-root`).
- Default scan roots: `~` (override with `--scan-roots <dirs...>`).
- Shows a dry-run plan and asks for confirmation before executing.
- JSON logging: pass `--log-json out.json` to append JSON Lines of planned/applied actions.

Example
`slm --data-root ~/Developer/Data --scan-roots ~ ~/Developer --dry-run --log-json ./slm-actions.jsonl`

Safety
- Only directory symlinks are considered.
- Broken symlinks are ignored.
- Cross-device moves fall back to copy+delete.

Logging example (JSON Lines + jq)
```
TMP=$(mktemp -d)
mkdir -p "$TMP/Data/Target" "$TMP/Home"
ln -s "$TMP/Data/Target" "$TMP/Home/my-link"

# Preview and log actions
slm --data-root "$TMP/Data" --scan-roots "$TMP/Home" \
    --dry-run --log-json "$TMP/slm-actions.jsonl"

# Inspect log (one JSON object per line)
jq . "$TMP/slm-actions.jsonl"
jq -r '.type' "$TMP/slm-actions.jsonl"   # prints: move, retarget, ...
```
